project_descrip: Short: BURA IRRIGATION AND SETTLEMENT SCHEME REHABILITATION Long: The proposed project aims to improve the livelihood of the residents of Bora region and to settle about 2,500 farming families, by restoring irrigation systems, drainage and basic irrigation and irrigation facilities to an area of about 5,500 hectares located on the west bank of the Tana River in the southeast of the country. agencyname: Kuwait Fund for Arab Economic Development (KFAED)
projecttitle: AL-MURJAH IRREGATION IN LOKOAS AREA PROJECT.
project_descrip: Short: AL-MURJAH IRREGATION IN LOKOAS AREA PROJECT. Long: The project consists of construction of a pumping station of a capacity of about 3.6 CM/S, Construction of 3  reservoirs with a total capacity of about 4000 CM, installation of connecting pipelines with a total length of about 4.8 and Diameter of 10001400 mm, construction of elevated irrigation canals of a total length of about 112 Km and semicircular cross section of  a diameter 4002000 mm. The Project also includes river training works of  Buhrira River to accommodate additional drainage water, construction of drainage canals of a total length of about 70 Km and installation of subsurface drainage system with a total length of about 1100 Km and diameter of about 65 mm, construction of asphalted road of about 8 Km  long and field roads of about 33 Km, in addition to installation of 15 Km power lines, provision of agricultural support and consultancy services.
shortdescription: AL-MURJAH IRREGATION IN LOKOAS AREA PROJECT.
longdescription: The project consists of construction of a pumping station of a capacity of about 3.6 CM/S, Construction of 3  reservoirs with a total capacity of about 4000 CM, installation of connecting pipelines with a total length of about 4.8 and Diameter of 10001400 mm, construction of elevated irrigation canals of a total length of about 112 Km and semicircular cross section of  a diameter 4002000 mm. The Project also includes river training works of  Buhrira River to accommodate additional drainage water, construction of drainage canals of a total length of about 70 Km and installation of subsurface drainage system with a total length of about 1100 Km and diameter of about 65 mm, construction of asphalted road of about 8 Km  long and field roads of about 33 Km, in addition to installation of 15 Km power lines, provision of agricultural support and consultancy services.

agencyname: Kuwait Fund for Arab Economic Development (KFAED)
projecttitle: TAMLOT DAM FOR IRRIGATION AND WATER SUPPLY
project_descrip: Short: TAMLOT DAM FOR IRRIGATION AND WATER SUPPLY Long: The Project consists of the construction of a roller compacted concreteweight dam on Insekmer river the dam will be about 320 m long and 7 meters wide and with a height of 60 meters and storage capacity of about 50 million m3.  The project also includes the construction of concrete spillway 90 m in length with a design flow of about 750 m3 /second, bottom evacuation 2.2 meter in diameter with a design flow of about 60 m3 /second and irrigation and potable water intakes in addition to the consulting services for detailed engineering and supervision of the Project

projecttitle: Irrigation Systems Improvement Project (In Eastern And Central Regions Of NEPAL)
project_descrip: Short: IRRIGATION SYSTEMS IMPROVEMENT PROJECT (IN EASTERN AND CENTRAL REGIONS OF NEPAL) Long: The project aims to support economic and social development in the eastern and central regions of Nepal in particular and the rest of the country in general by rehabilitating and expanding existing irrigation systems managed by farmers with the aim of securing sufficient quantities of irrigation water, thereby increasing and sustaining agricultural production of about 7600 hectares. Agricultural land, thus contributing to poverty reduction for the people of the immediate impact area of the project in addition to contributing to national food security.

agencyname: Kuwait Fund for Arab Economic Development (KFAED)
projecttitle: THE REHAB./CONST. OF IRRIGATION NET. AND DRAINAGE SYS. IN DJIZAKH AND SYRDARYA
project_descrip: Short: THE REHAB./CONST. OF IRRIGATION NET. AND DRAINAGE SYS. IN DJIZAKH AND SYRDARYA Long: The Project consists of works of rehabilitation, construction and improvement of irrigation and drainage networks in each of Syrdarya and Djizakh regions.  The Syrdarya region works includes rehabilitation of irrigation networks of a total length of about 347 km including major secondary and tertiary canals with all civil and mechanical works.  It also includes drainage structures with a total length of 268 km, construction of 50 vertical drainage structures.  Djizakh region works includes construction of a new pumping station with all relevant electrical and mechanical structures, the construction of irrigation canal with a total length of about 15 km and the rehabilitation of a drainage canal of a length of about 68 km.  The project also includes environmental mitigation works, institutional support, demonstration farms, project implementation unit, workshop and consultancy services for detailed design, tender documents and supervision of construction.
shortdescription: THE REHAB./CONST. OF IRRIGATION NET. AND DRAINAGE SYS. IN DJIZAKH AND SYRDARYA
channelreportedname: MINISTRY OF AGRICULTURE AND WATER RESOURCES

The Syrdarya region works includes rehabilitation of irrigation networks of a total length of about 347 km including major secondary and tertiary canals with all civil and mechanical works.  It also includes drainage structures with a total length of 268 km, construction of 50 vertical drainage structures.  Djizakh region works includes construction of a new pumping station with all relevant electrical and mechanical structures, the construction of irrigation canal with a total length of about 15 km and the rehabilitation of a drainage canal of a length of about 68 km.  The project also includes environmental mitigation works, institutional support, demonstration farms, project implementation unit, workshop and consultancy services for detailed design, tender documents and supervision of construction.

project_descrip: Short: GUZAR-CHIM- KUKDALA HIGHWAY Long: The Government of Uzbekistan has applied to the Fund to contribute to the financing of the 'Gozar-Shim-Kokdala' highway project.The proposed project aims to support the openness and economic and social activity of the central and southern regions of Uzbekistan, and to meet the demand for internal transport in the project area and regional commercial traffic.The project includes the construction of a asphalt highway of about 73 km long with four lanes wide 3.75 meters per lane, and with paved outer side shoulders 2.5 meters wide .The project road will be equipped with regular intersections of more than one level, bridges over irrigation canals, drainage facilities and safety and environmental protection supplies. The project also includes consulting services and institutional support for the project implementation unit.

projecttitle: Rural Infrastructure Development Project In Ha Tinh Province
project_descrip: Short: RURAL INFRASTRUCTURE DEVELOPMENT PROJECT IN HA TINH PROVINCE Long: The Government of the Socialist Republic of Vietnam has applied to IFAD to contribute to the financing of the Rural Infrastructure Development Project in Hatten Province, which is responsible for the overall supervision of its implementation by the People's Committee of Hatten Province through its Rural Development Projects Management Unit, while its operation and maintenance will be carried out by the People's Committee through Local organs affiliated in the provinces and communities in the various project sites. The proposed project aims at supporting the economic and social development and combating poverty in these two regions by developing and rehabilitating rural infrastructure including irrigation systems and rural roads, improving and diversifying agricultural production, reducing the costs of transporting crops and production inputs, as well as facilitating people's access to social services in the region. .

longdescription: The project aims to support economic and social development in Hai Hu Province, Nam Dun province of the Republic of Vietnam, by providing irrigation and agricultural drainage services, thereby contributing to the increase and sustainability of agricultural production, thereby contributing to reducing poverty for the people of the immediate impact zone of the project. Their current population is about 105,000, in addition to contributing to food security at the national level.
